Given I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'MRI pelvic floor' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 03 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
Then I go to Page 08 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Sigmoid diverticular disease' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Hansen and Stock' checkbox is enabled
And 'Classification of diverticular disease (CDD)/S2k' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sigmoid carcinoma' radio button is enabled
And 'Auto inflammatory diverticulitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Appendagitis epiploica' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Hansen and Stock' checkbox
Then 'Stage 1: Acute, uncomplicated diverticulitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage 2: Acute, complicated diverticulitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage 2a: Peridiverticulitis, phlegmonous diverticulitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage 2b: Abscess diverticulitis, covered perforation' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage 2c: Free perforation' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage 3: Chronic recurrent diverticulitis' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Classification of diverticular disease (CDD)/S2k' checkbox
Then 'Type 1: Acute, uncomplicated diverticulitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 2: Acute, complicated diverticulitis with phlegmonous reaction of surrounding tissue' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 3: Chronic diverticular disease; recurrent or persistent symptomatic diverticular disease' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 4: Diverticular bleeding' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Type 1: Acute, uncomplicated diverticulitis' radio button
Then 'Type 1a: Diverticulitis without perifocal soft tissue reaction' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 1b: Diverticulitis with phlegmonous environmental reaction' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Type 2: Acute, complicated diverticulitis with phlegmonous reaction of surrounding tissue' radio button
Then 'Type 2a: Microabscess, covered perforation, small abscess (â‰¤ 1 cm); minimal paracolic air' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 2b: Macroabscess, covered perforation, para- or mesocolic abscess (> 1 cm)' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 2c: Free perforation, free air/liquid; generalized peritonitis' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Type 3: Chronic diverticular disease; recurrent or persistent symptomatic diverticular disease' radio button
Then 'Type 3a: Symptomatic uncomplicated diverticular disease (SUDD)' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 3b: Recurrent diverticulitis without complications; signs of inflammation (laboratory) present' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 3c: Recurrent diverticulitis with complications; detection of stenoses, fistulas, conglomerate' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Sigmoid carcinoma' radio button
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Auto inflammatory diverticulitis' radio button
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Appendagitis epiploica' radio button
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled


